<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-6 sm:py-8" style="view-transition-name: page-content;">
  <%= render "shared/navbar", title: "SETTINGS", current: "settings" %>

  <!-- Sample Bulletin Video -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-6">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-base-content/50">Sample Bulletin</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/60 mb-3">Watch an example of what a daily Me News bulletin looks like:</p>
      <div class="aspect-[9/16] max-w-xs mx-auto rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg">
        <iframe
          src="https://customer-umftpj9wolekeelh.cloudflarestream.com/b4db1f92c0ef358622add4241742aa4e/iframe?autoplay=false&muted=false&loop=false&controls=true"
          allow="autoplay; encrypted-media"
          class="w-full h-full border-0"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Card -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-sm mb-6">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-base-content/50">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="join join-vertical w-full mt-2">
        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" checked="checked" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What is Me News?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            Me News is social media that feels social again. You get little updates from friends and family — packaged into a fun daily "news report" with an AI host. Instead of an endless feed, it's one shared episode for your group.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">Why does Me News exist?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            <p>Because modern social media is great… and also exhausting.</p>
            <p class="mt-2">At some point, it stopped being social and became just media: an endless scroll of content that's just interesting enough to keep you engaged, while we somehow feel more connected and more isolated at the same time.</p>
            <p class="mt-2">Research using American National Election Studies data argues overall platform use declined from 2020 to 2024, with the youngest and oldest Americans increasingly abstaining.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What do I actually do in the app?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            <p>You post short videos to your friend group. Then Me News:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-1">
              <li>turns them into a daily report (script + captions)</li>
              <li>shares the finished episode back to the group</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2">It's like "Daily Dose of Internet" — but for your group.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">How is this different from a group chat?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            <p>Group chats are great, but they're messy. Me News gives you:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-1">
              <li>a shared format (a daily episode)</li>
              <li>a reason to watch (it's short + entertaining)</li>
              <li>a way to respond (without comment-section energy)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What's the "STOP SCROLLING" part?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            Me News isn't trying to be a feed. It's the opposite: one daily drop, then you go live your life.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">How does Me News handle the "no content = no users" problem?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            <p>Social apps hit the cold start problem (also described by the 90-9-1 participation pattern: most people watch, a few contribute). Me News tackles it like this:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mt-1">
              <li>The AI journalist looks for stories inside your circle — it asks questions and collects reactions (often via simple prompts, like replying to a message).</li>
              <li>It's a safe space — more like a chat group. Your videos don't "escape" into the internet.</li>
              <li>Lower friction to post — quick clips are encouraged, and using generative tools is welcomed.</li>
              <li>The TikTok insight: add music + framing and mundane becomes watchable. A small clip feels more interesting when it's part of a "show."</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">How do replies work?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            <p>Instead of waiting for comments, Me News asks the group questions about the videos — like a playful interview. You can reply:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-1">
              <li>by text (chat-style)</li>
              <li>or by sending a video response</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">Is it private?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            Yes — the default is friends + family only. It's designed to feel closer to a group chat than a public timeline (no viral mechanics, no strangers, no performance).
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">Is Me News "AI-powered social media"?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            That's the bet: the AI isn't the content — your friends are the content. The AI is the producer/host that turns small moments into something you'll actually watch.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse collapse-arrow join-item border border-base-300">
          <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
          <div class="collapse-title font-medium text-sm">What's next?</div>
          <div class="collapse-content text-sm text-base-content/60">
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
              <li>Better UI</li>
              <li>More ways to interact + more AI generated content</li>
              <li>Upgraded visuals</li>
              <li>Tighter "interview" flow so responses feel effortless</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Sign Out -->
  <% if current_user %>
    <div class="mb-6">
      <%= button_to "Sign Out", auth_logout_path, method: :delete, class: "btn btn-outline btn-error w-full" %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
